Media Queries -At-rules
@import
@media

Media queries are used to conditionally apply CSS styles with the CSS @media and @import at-rules and in JavaScript to test and monitor media states such as with the matchMedia() method, matches property, and change event. Media queries are used as values of the <link>, <source>, and <style> HTML element media attributes, conditionally applying the link, source, or style if the media query is true

Grid-The grid CSS property is a shorthand property that sets all of the explicit and implicit grid properties in a single declaration.
The grid-template-areas CSS property specifies named grid areas, establishing the cells in the grid and assigning them names.
